    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pictorial records of events kept by Lakota and other Plains Native tribes, usually on a yearly cycle. Primarily painted on buffalo hides. Some of the earliest winter counts date from the 1600s.</Note_Text>
